==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intervale
<hw>In"ter*vale</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A tract of low ground between
hills, or along the banks of a stream, usually alluvial land, enriched
by the overflowings of the river, or by fertilizing deposits of earth
from the adjacent hills. Cf. <er>Bottom</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 7.</def>
<mark>[Local, U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The woody <qex>intervale</qex> just beyond the marshy land.</q>
<rj><qau>The Century.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intervallum</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
